HEADWORD: bakshis
<hw>bakshis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A relatively small
amount of money given for services rendered (as by a waiter). Same as
<er>Backsheesh</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gratuity, tip, baksheesh, bakshish,
backsheesh.</syn>⟦br⟧
